Hoping to stand in the way of a  U.S. victory are seasoned pros Hideki Matsuyama, Adam Scott, Louis Oosthuizen and more. The contest will unfold at Royal Melbourne Golf Club, home to the Presidents Cup in 2011 and 1998 when the Internationals claimed their only victory in the series.Welcome to the official YouTube channel of the PGA TOUR.Here you can find everything you need to stay up to date with the world‚Äôs foremost golf tour. description: This video is sponsored by Keeps!Go to https://keeps.com/hilow to get 50% off your first order of hair loss treatment. 2 out of 3 men will start to permanently lose their hair by 35 due to male pattern baldness. Keeps‚Äô treatments are up to 90% effective at reducing and stopping further hair loss.$1000 set of wheels and tires vs. $4000 set of wheels and tires. Does more expensive mean more better? And is it worth it?We bought two identical Nissan 350z coupes and have been modifying them to be FUN, daily drivers that you can take to the track. James Pumphrey and Zach Jobe are on Team Hi and their 350z gets the expensive parts. Nolan Sykes and Aaron Parker are on Team Low, and their 350z gets the cheap ones.For this episode Team Hi bought Advan RG3‚Äôs at $676 per wheel and Bridgestone Potenza RE71Rs at $265 per tire for a total of $3,764.Team Low went with XXR 527s at $127 per wheel and Federal 595 RS-RR at $136 per tire for a total of $1,052.The two teams will mount these wheel and tire setups on their newly lowered 350Zs and then take them out to the skidpad. We‚Äôll look at 0 to 60 times, stopping distances, how many Gs they can pull. Jordan|Jamie Foxx|O‚ÄôShea Jackson Jr.|Karan Kendrick|Gil Netter|Destin Daniel Cretton
description: Based on a true story, Michael B. Jordan, Jamie Foxx, and Brie Larson star in #JustMercy, in cinemas January 23, 2020. Michael B. Jordan (‚ÄúBlack Panther,‚Äù ‚ÄúCreed,‚Äù ‚ÄúCreed II‚Äù) and Oscar winners Jamie Foxx(‚ÄúRay,‚Äù ‚ÄúBaby Driver,‚Äù ‚ÄúDjango: Unchained‚Äù) and Brie Larson (‚ÄúRoom,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Glass Castle,‚Äù ‚ÄúCaptainMarvel‚Äù) star in ‚ÄúJust Mercy,‚Äù an inspiring drama that brings one of the most important stories ofour time to the big screen.Award-winning filmmaker Destin Daniel Cretton (‚ÄúThe Glass Castle,‚Äù ‚ÄúShort Term 12‚Äù)directed the film from a screenplay he co-wrote, based on the award-winning nonfiction bestsellerby Bryan Stevenson.A powerful and thought-provoking true story, ‚ÄúJust Mercy‚Äù follows young lawyer BryanStevenson (Jordan) and his history-making battle for justice. After graduating from Harvard, Bryanhad his pick of lucrative jobs. Instead, he heads to Alabama to defend those wrongly condemnedor who were not afforded proper representation, with the support of local advocate Eva Ansley(Larson). One of his first, and most incendiary, cases is that of Walter McMillian (Foxx), who, in1987, was sentenced to die for the notorious murder of an 18-year-old girl, despite apreponderance of evidence proving his innocence and the fact that the only testimony againsthim came from a criminal with a motive to lie. In the years that follow, Bryan becomes embroiledin a labyrinth of legal and political maneuverings and overt and unabashed racism as he fights forWalter, and others like him, with the odds‚Äîand the system‚Äîstacked against them.The main cast also includes Rob Morgan (‚ÄúMudbound‚Äù) as Herbert Richardson, a fellowprisoner who also sits on death row awaiting his fate; Tim Blake Nelson (‚ÄúWormwood‚Äù) as RalphMyers, whose pivotal testimony against Walter McMillian is called into question; Rafe Spall asTommy Chapman, the DA who is fighting to uphold Walter‚Äôs conviction and sentence; O‚ÄôSheaJackson Jr. (‚ÄúStraight Outta Compton‚Äù) as Anthony Ray Hinton, another wrongly convicted deathrow inmate whose cause is taken up by Bryan; and Karan Kendrick (‚ÄúThe Hate U Give‚Äù) as Walter‚Äôswife, Minnie McMillian, who stands by her husband.The film is produced by two-time Oscar nominee Gil Netter (‚ÄúLife of Pi,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Blind Side‚Äù),Asher Goldstein (‚ÄúShort Term 12‚Äù) and Michael B. Jordan. Bryan Stevenson, Mike Drake, Niija Kuykendall, Gabriel Hammond, Daniel Hammond, Scott Budnick, Jeff Skoll and Charles D. Kingserved as executive producers.Cretton co-wrote the screenplay with Andrew Lanham (‚ÄúThe Glass Castle‚Äù), based onStevenson‚Äôs book Just Mercy: A Story of Justice and Redemption. Published in 2014 by Spiegel &Grau, the book has spent more than 150 weeks on The New York Times Best Sellers List, andcounting. It was also named one of the year‚Äôs best books by a number of top publications,including TIME Magazine. For the book, Stevenson also won the Andrew Carnegie Medal forExcellence, an NAACP Image Award, and the Dayton Literary Peace Prize for Nonfiction.Cretton‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team included director of photography Brett Pawlak,production designer Sharon Seymour, editor Nat Sanders and composer Joel P. West, all of whompreviously collaborated with the director on ‚ÄúThe Glass Castle.‚Äù They are joined by costumedesigner Francine Jamison-Tanchuck (‚ÄúDetroit,‚Äù ‚ÄúRoman J. Israel, Esq.‚Äù).Warner Bros. Pictures presents, in Association with Endeavor Content/OneCommunity/Participant Media/Macro, a Gil Netter Production, an Outlier Society Production, ‚ÄúJustMercy.‚Äù Slated for release on January 23, 2020, ‚ÄúJust Mercy‚Äù will be distributedworldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.

description: SpaceX is targeting Thursday, December 5 for launch of its nineteenth Commercial Resupply Services mission (CRS-19) at 12:29 p.m. EST, or 17:29 UTC, from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at Cape Canaveral Air Force Station, Florida. Dragon will separate from Falcon 9‚Äôs second stage about nine minutes after liftoff and attach to the space station on Saturday, December 7. The Dragon spacecraft that will support the CRS-19 mission previously supported the CRS-4 mission in September 2014 and the CRS-11 mission in June 2017. Following stage separation, SpaceX will attempt to recover Falcon 9‚Äôs first stage on the Of Course I Still Love You droneship, which will be stationed in the Atlantic Ocean.

description: Hey guys! Today I am revisiting my shrink plastic obsession (or shrinky dinks. ehhhh) and making 12 different food/animal themed DIY custom pins. I hope you gys are into this, because I looooove making these things, it's so much fun!! This is pretty easy to do, but there are a lot of steps, and it can be a bit time consuming. But, if you're looking for an awesome craft that involves drawing, you've got it. These are super cute in the end and create such a cool collection to display on pin boards, bags or clothing.RAINBOW PICKLE SHIRT: NO LONGER AVAILABLE.ENAMEL PINS:https://me-merch.myshopify.com/collections/hard-enamel-pinsMATERIALS FOR THIS PROJECT *contains affiliate links*:Shrink Plastic: https://amzn.to/35KHT7yPosca Paint Pens: https://amzn.to/2Y3wcX4Dimensional Magic: https://amzn.to/37LpMjzMini Oven?
